  "title": "Front-end Developer",
  "description": "<p>‌</p><p><strong>Position Overview</strong></p><p>We are seeking a highly skilled ‌<strong>Senior Front-End Developer </strong>with expertise in React to join our dynamic engineering team. As a key contributor, you will collaborate with designers, back-end developers, and product teams to build scalable, performant, and user-friendly web applications. The ideal candidate will bring deep technical knowledge, and a passion for delivering high-quality digital experiences.<br /></p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong>‌</h3><ul><li>Design and develop modern, responsive web applications using ‌<strong>React (including Next.js, React Router, and hooks)</strong>‌.</li><li>Optimize front-end performance through code minification, lazy loading, and efficient state management (e.g., Redux, Context API).</li><li>Implement reusable UI components and patterns using libraries like Material-UI, Chakra UI, or custom solutions.</li><li>Integrate with back-end services via RESTful APIs or GraphQL, ensuring seamless data flow.</li><li>Write unit and integration tests using Jest/Testing Library to maintain code reliability.</li><li>Collaborate with UX designers to translate wireframes into pixel-perfect interfaces.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Qualifications & Requirements</strong>‌</p><ul><li>‌3<strong>+ </strong>years‌ of professional front-end development experience, with ‌2<strong>+ </strong>years specializing in React‌.</li><li>Proficient in JavaScript/ES6+, HTML5, CSS3, and Sass/Less.</li><li>Strong understanding of React lifecycle, fiber architecture, and reconciliation process.</li><li>Experience with state management (Redux, Zustand, or MobX) and routing (React Router).</li><li>Familiarity with build tools (Webpack, Vite, Parcel) and bundling optimization.</li><li>Knowledge of accessibility (WCAG), SEO principles, and cross-browser compatibility.</li><li>Ability to debug performance issues using Chrome DevTools, Lighthouse, or WebPageTest.</li><li>Experience with CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI) and version control (Git).</li><li>Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to work in agile environments (Scrum/Kanban).</li><li>Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or equivalent practical experience.</li></ul><p></p>",
